alo - Ardour Lirc Osc

ABOUT
This is a very simple mapper between lirc and Ardour's OSC written in Perl.

DEPENDENCIES
It's based on Audio-Ardour-Control and Lirc-Client perl modules available at cpan.org.

CONFIGURATION
You need a properly configured lirc remote and a specific lirc configuration file in your "~/.lirc/" named "alo".
The example provided is for an ATI Remote Wonder.

USAGE
Don't forget to enable OSC in ardour before launching alo with "perl alo.pl"
